extends template.jade

block title
   title= title_start + "Why do it?"

block content
   h1 Why do debating?
   article
      h2 It's Fun!
      div.adjustive-flex
         div.adjustive-flex
            +image("images/student-debate.jpg", 500/2, 311/2, "Student teacher debate", "images/full/student-debate.jpg").float-left
            +image("images/teacher-debate.jpg", 500/2, 311/2, "Student teacher debate", "images/full/teacher-debate.jpg").float-right
      p.center
         | No really, it's actually fun.
   article
      h2 Learning
      p
         | Not only will you learn about many various topics, but you'll also develop very transferable skills such as public speaking, developing arguments and thinking on your feet. If you think you're already pretty confident with speaking, well that's great, debating is another way to test yourself and learn more.
   article
      h2 Friends
      p
         | Of course you can and should make a team with your friends, and this is a great extra way to work together with them and learn and have fun. You may even make new friends who share common interests.
   article
      h2 Competition
      p
         | Every few weeks there is a round of debating against high school teams around Hamilton (and a little further away). As these rounds progress, the best teams will be put into quarter-finals, semi-finals, and final-finals.
      p
         | There is also the Waikato Russel McVeagh debating competition, which we have recently done 
         a(href="http://www.hbhs.school.nz/News/HBHS-Senior-Debating-Team-win-Russell-McVeagh-Competition") very well in.
         |  From this competition, there are various opportunities to move onto further national and international competitions.
      p
         | Every year a senior and junior debating team from HBHS are sent to compete in the 
         a(href="http://www.super8.co.nz/") Super 8
         |  competition against 7 other boys' schools from around the North Island. Doing well in this helps the school in the competition and gives a chance to travel away from school for a couple of days.
      p
         | Debating is a pathway which can lead you all around the world to compete at the highest level, representing your country.
   article
      h2 Service Opportunities
      p
         | Experienced senior debaters have the opportunity to do adjudication for junior debates. As well as helping out and gaining service hours, you will also assuredly learn a lot from this to help you further with debating.